  "notes": "When this is the danced after a Forward Lock, one walk on S is added (Man RF fwd, Lady LF back)\nPrepping the walk: get to knees, hip rotate to R, which gives more room to move as well.\nWhen the Progressive Chassé is danced after an underturned Natural Spin Turn or an Impetus Turn as an entry to the Quick Open Reverse, the normal alignment of the Progressive Chassé will be (from Man's view):\n1. Backing DC against LOD\n2. Pointing DC\n3,4,5 Facing DC.\nWhen the Progressive Chassé is taken after a Natural Spin turn danced with normal alignment it will be:\n1 Backing DC\n2 Pointing to LOD\n3,4,5 Facing LOD",
